parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Tank Delamination and Coating Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delamination of the fuel tank and failure of the internal coating can cause fuel line, fuel pump, and fuel injector clogging, leading to loss of power, stalling, and engine failure, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: and stalls while driving; the fuel filter
and fuel injectors become clogged; the engine sputters and loses power under load; the fuel tank needs to be replaced

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Failure due to Coolant Leak into Crankcase
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The leakage of coolant into the crankcase can cause engine damage, leading to costly repairs, and potentially resulting in engine failure, which can cause accidents or leave the driver stranded.
Engine fires can cause damage to the vehicle and surrounding property, and can potentially lead to injuries or fatalities.
The failure of the fan belt can cause loss of steering and brakes, leading to accidents or loss of control of the vehicle.

The melting of the electrical connector at the central junction can cause a range of electrical system failures, including loss of power to essential systems, increasing the risk of accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: burning smell or smoke from the connector.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The premature failure of the alternator can cause the vehicle's battery to drain, leading to a loss of power to essential systems, increasing the risk of accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
